               <msContents>
                  <summary>The contract calls for the making of a wagon yoke and a basket, both to be of good quality, by the carpenter Petes. These are to be delivered withinh nine months. The contact was executed on Pharmouthi 5th, which places it in late April at that time.  The contract was drawn up in Pathyris in the Thebaid in the notarial office of Ammonios (cf. P.Lond. II 218, p. 15). A Horus, son of Nechoutes, is known from P.Lond. III 1204, p. 11.</summary>
